@mattyglesias
 14h14 hours ago
"Germans are weirded out by the idea of a minority government but Merkel is popular and CDU holds the central ideological position on almost every issue. I think it’ll work out fine."

First, the CDU/CSU are now well ahead of the Social Democrats, so Merkel will get the first chance to form a government. At this point, she may have two options:
 - form a coalition with the Free Democrats, if this guarantees a majority. Recently, the CDU/CSU+ Free Democrats get more votes than a red-red-green coalition;
 - offer the Social Democrats to reconstitute the Grand Coalition, with or without the Free Democrats. This might be necessary if CDS/CSU/FD do not have a majority (and neither do the red-red-green coalition, owing to the presence of Alternative for Deutschland). At this point, Shulz can't say no.
